 more information contact suzuki at   between  am and  pm pt monday through friday or visit the firms website at wwwsuzukicyclescom recall details description and models this recall is for the following suzuki kingquad models all  to  ltax models all  to  ltax models all  to  ltax models and  ltax and ltax models manufactured before december   the words suzuki kingquad are on the left and right sides of the fuel tank housing model numbers are on the left and right lower side panels above the footrests   remedy consumers should immediately stop using these vehicles and contact a local suzuki atv dealer to schedule an appointment for a free repair consumers with  ltax and ltax models should call their local suzuki atv dealer to determine if their atv is subject to this recall consumers with recalled atvs are being sent a notice directly from suzuki incidentsinjuries american suzuki has received  reports of fuel leaking from the recalled atvs no injuries have been reported sold at suzuki atv dealers nationwide from july  through february  for between  and  manufacturers suzuki manufacturing of america corporation distributors american suzuki motor corp of brea california montgomery motors ltd of honolulu hawaii suzuki del caribe inc of rio piedras puerto rico manufactured in united states units about  report an incident involving this product the us consumer product safety commission is charged with protecting the public from unreasonable risks of injury or death associated with the use of thousands of types of consumer products under the agency’s jurisdiction deaths injuries and property damage from consumer product incidents cost the nation more than  trillion annually cpsc is committed to protecting consumers and families from products that pose a fire electrical chemical or mechanical hazard cpscs work to help ensure the safety of consumer products  such as toys cribs power tools cigarette lighters and household chemicals – contributed to a decline in the rate of d